
/*
 * 1. The [strings.split] slot is used here to divide the value of the [query] node—located as a child of the [.arguments] node—into separate strings, using a single space (" ") as the delimiter.  
 * 2. The expression `:x:@.arguments/*/query` retrieves the [query] node, so its value becomes the source string for splitting.  
 * 3. Each substring between spaces in the original [query] value becomes a new child node under [strings.split], effectively tokenizing the input string by whitespace.
 * 
 * Use Cases:
 * - Parsing a search query from user input into individual keywords for further processing.
 * - Splitting a sentence into words to perform word-level analysis or filtering.
 * - Tokenizing command-line arguments or input parameters separated by spaces.
 * - Preparing a list of tags or identifiers provided as a space-delimited string.
 */
strings.split:x:@.arguments/*/query
   .:" "
